features: BEST FOR BABY: What makes our diapers best for baby? Nappychat diapers are soft and flexible for a comfortable fit; keeping baby snug and dry for up to 12 hours.

SAFE FOR DELICATE SKIN: They’re free from perfumes, lotions & latex, and are dermatologically tested making them suitable for newborns. Nappychat diapers are hypoallergenic and dermatologically tested; free from added chemicals, perfumes, lotions and latex making them soft and gentle even on the most delicate skin.

PLAYFUL AND FUN: Every Mum & You diaper features a playful tribe of nappychat characters to help you bond with your baby at change time and beyond. They provide inspiration for songs and stories for your little ones – they’re a great way to spark little imaginations!

ECO-FRIENDLY: What makes our nappies eco-friendly? The soft as cotton core is made using chlorine-free wood pulp from PEFC certified sustainable forestry. They’re made using 100% renewable energy, and the packaging is 100% recyclable and contains 30% recycled content.

AT MUM & YOU WE ARE ON A JOURNEY - not only to have a positive impact on the lives of moms and babies, but also to continuously improve the sustainability of our products. We’re constantly reviewing and innovating new ways to offer sustainability without compromising quality or convenience.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Here at Mum & You, we are committed to making this wild parenting adventure a little bit easier. Our mission is to enable and support moms, resulting in kids living healthy lives, living to reach their full potential. There are no white lab coats to be seen at M&Y HQ. All of our products are designed by our team of Moms, with you in mind.

Leak free for up to 12 hours A super absorbent core locks moisture away from your baby's skin and guards against leaks for up to 12 hours, because we know there’s more to life than changing baby, soggy clothes & beds Kind to the planet A biodegradable core, zero glue and less wood pulp than other diapers means we cut down fewer trees and look after today's world for tomorrow’s generation. Hypoallergenic & Dermatologically Tested Free from harsh chemicals and made using biodegradable wood pulp from sustainable forestry. So they’re kind to your baby’s skin and the environment. Plus, it's soft, like down with no rustling or stiff edges.

Nappychat was developed 3 key objectives in mind: Inspire - Develop - Bond Content designed for each of your child’s stages: 0-9 months - When the sun comes up a new day starts. What happens next? Wake up, get up, have diaper changed…9-18 months - What do bananas look like? What is their color?Over 18 months - What do we put on when it's cold? Why do we put it on? reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Bigger than I thought!
reviews.reviewText: I accidently bought the wrong size and based on the weight listed on the package, they should have leaked! However we've only had one leak out of a whole pack of 72 diapers. Size 2 says up to 13 lbs but my daughter is 15 pounds! Great find!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 12, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very soft, convenient shipping
reviews.reviewText: These diapers are super soft and stretchy. The size 2 fits perfectly on my 2 month old who is 11 lbs. We live in a rural area so it’s super convenient that these come right to the door and not the PO Box.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not for a newborn
reviews.reviewText: Update 2/6/2019These diapers leak if your baby has a blow out. They leak out of the leg holes it soaks through the fabric and goes everywhere. I put a new diaper on my 2 week old breastfed newborn and in 15 minutes it was leaking out all over her. Only for blow outs it seems I don't have an issue with urine leaking out. Disappointing still bringing my review down to 3 stars.The diapers are soft but they are not meant for newborns. My daughter is 2 weeks old and 9lbs and they are pretty big on her. We will have to see how they hold up or if they will leak. They seem to have good contact all around there are no gaps but I was sad they weren't just a little smaller. No idea how anyone with a 7lbs baby could fit these on their child. Sizing definitely needs to be updated.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 30, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality, so soft!
reviews.reviewText: So soft! Amazing quality!! Just wish they had an indicator on whether baby peed as that is essential to monitor in a newborns first few weeks. Otherwise, love them. They’re very plush and soft and do not leak.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 15, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I am in love with this diapers. They are so soft, they absorb well and don't get baggy. This product is worth the price. I will be buying more.
